1. General Commands

docker version : Check the installed Docker version.

docker info : Display detailed system-wide information about Docker.

docker help : Display a list of Docker commands or help for a specific command.

2. Image Management
docker images : List all locally available Docker images.

docker pull <image> : Download an image from a registry (e.g., Docker Hub).

docker build -t <image-name>:<tag> . : Build an image from a Dockerfile in the current directory.

docker tag <image> <new-image-name>:<new-tag> : Tag an image with a new name or tag.

docker rmi <image> : Remove one or more images.

3. Container Management
docker ps : List running containers.

docker ps -a : List all containers (running and stopped).

docker run <image> : Start a container from an image.

docker run -d <image> : Start a container in detached mode (background).

docker run -it <image> : Start an interactive terminal session inside a container.

docker stop <container> : Stop a running container.

docker start <container> : Start a stopped container.

docker restart <container> : Restart a running container.

docker rm <container> : Remove one or more stopped containers.


4. Logs and Debugging
docker logs <container> : View logs of a container.

docker exec <container> <command> : Execute a command inside a running container.

docker inspect <container> : Display detailed information about a container.

docker stats: Show real-time resource usage of containers.

7. Cleanup Commands
docker system prune: Remove unused data (containers, images, volumes, etc.).

docker image prune: Remove dangling (unused) images.

docker container prune: Remove stopped containers.
